  "prompt_text": "What are some high-protein snacks I can buy at the store?",
  "provider": "groq",
  "model": "llama-3.3-70b-versatile",
  "response_text": "There are many high-protein snack options available at stores. Here are some popular ones:\n\n1. **Nuts and Seeds**: Almonds, cashews, pumpkin seeds, and chia seeds are all high in protein. Look for unsalted or low-sodium options.\n2. **Jerky**: Beef, turkey, or chicken jerky is a convenient and protein-rich snack. Choose low-sodium or sugar-free options.\n3. **Greek Yogurt**: Individual cups of Greek yogurt are a great source of protein. Look for brands with 15-20 grams of protein per serving.\n4. **Hard-Boiled Eggs**: Many stores now sell pre-cooked, hard-boiled eggs that are a convenient and protein-rich snack.\n5. **Cottage Cheese**: Single-serve cups of cottage cheese are a great source of protein. Look for brands with 25-30 grams of protein per serving.\n6. **Protein Bars**: Look for bars with at least 15 grams of protein and minimal added sugars. Some popular brands include Clif, Quest, and RXBAR.\n7. **Edamame**: Steamed or roasted edamame are a tasty and protein-rich snack. You can find them in the frozen food section or at some health food stores.\n8. **Protein Shakes**: Many stores now sell pre-made protein shakes or protein powder that you can mix with water or milk.\n9. **Meat Snacks**: Snack sticks, such as Slim Jim or Oberto, are a convenient source of protein.\n10. **Hummus and Veggie Sticks**: While not as high in protein as other options, hummus with veggie sticks like carrots or bell peppers can still provide a decent amount of protein.\n11. **Protein-Fortified Granola**: Some granolas are fortified with protein, making them a tasty and protein-rich snack.\n12. **Turkey or Chicken Slices**: Pre-sliced turkey or chicken breast can be a convenient and protein-rich snack.\n\nWhen shopping for high-protein snacks, be sure to check the nutrition label to ensure that the snack meets your protein needs and doesn't exceed your daily limits for added sugars, sodium, and saturated fats.",
